<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Abominable Snowman,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Climber Resumes Search For Abominable Snowman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British mountain climber set off for the
Himalayas to find out whether the Abominable Snowman is myth or
monster.
   Chris Bonington, who left London on Wednesday, intends to return
to the 23,237-foot Menglungtse, where last year he found footprints
from an unidentified creature on a failed attempt to climb the
mountain.
   ``It would be fantastic if we could come back with some proof,''
he said during a visit to the Natural History Museum in London
before his departure.
   Bonington and a five-man team discovered 7-inch-by-4-inch
footprints 16,000 feet up the mountain last year. Periodic
sightings of the creature, also known as the yeti, have been
reported for decades.
</TEXT>
