<HEAD>Energy Minister Denies Big Kenyan Oil Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A newspaper said vast oil deposits have
been found in northern Kenya, but the minister of energy downplayed
the discovery.
   ``It is true that encouraging results have been achieved, but
conclusions drawn by the paper are rather grossly exaggerated,''
Nicholas Biwott said.
   Biwott issued a statement Wednesday after the Kenya Times
reported the energy minister had confirmed the presence of vast oil
deposits and had said that Kenya was ready to begin looking for
pump sites.
   The newspaper of the governing Kenya African National Union
Party also quoted Biwott as saying two of five international
companies prospecting in Kenya had struck oil.
   Biwott said test wells in the northern Turkana, Marsabit and
Isiolo districts had confirmed the presence of gas and oil, but
none of the wells had ``yielded hydrocarbons in commercial
quantities.''
</TEXT>
