   She's three times the age of many of her co-dancers and the
oldest ballerina of stature performing today. But Plisetskaya
nonetheless is living up to the advance publicity generated by
organizers of Making Music Together, the largest Soviet-U.S.
cultural exchange ever staged.
   Although other artists also have drawn capacity crowds since the
three-week festival opened March 11, Plisetksaya has reigned
supreme among the 285 featured Soviet performers as crowd-pleasers
go.
   A capacity audience of 4,100 crowded Boston's Wang Center for
the Performing Arts for a performance based on Bizet's ``Carmen''
Tuesday, clearly enjoying the grace of Nina Ananiashvili, the
strength of Adris Liepe and the near flawless mastery of other
