<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Japan-Markets     03-31 0184</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Dips, Stocks Lose Ground in Tokyo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar dropped nearly one yen against the
Japanese currency in Tokyo trading Thursday, while stock prices
declined slightly after three days of substantial gains.
   The dollar opened at 125.15 yen and slumped to 124.50 yen at the
close, down 0.93 yen from Wednesday's close of 125.43 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which rose 366.89 points on Wednesday to a
post-crash high, slipped 59.81 points, closing at 26,260.26 points.
   ``Fiscal year-end demand for dollars, which supported the dollar
in early trading, has come to an end,'' said an official of a major
commercial bank in Tokyo, who spoke on condition of anonymity. The
Japanese fiscal year ends Thursday.
   On the stock exchange, traders said the market has come to a
rest after three days of sharp gains.
   The Nikkei Stock Average surged more than 1,000 points in the
previous three sessions. Wednesday's close of the stock market's
key barometer was 26,319.98 points, the first close above 26,000
since last October's market crash.
</TEXT>
