<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0498</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Storm Dumps Snow From Utah to Great Plains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm packing winds up to 40 mph swirled around the Rockies
today, spreading more than 5 inches of snow from Utah to the Great
Plains.
   Rain fell across the Tennessee and lower Mississippi valleys,
prompting flash flood watches in parts of Mississippi and Louisiana
where recent rain left the ground saturated.
   Forecasters said up to 2 feet of snow were expected in the
foothills of the Colorado Rockies by Friday morning. So far, more
than 5 inches have fallen at Fort Collins, Colo., and more than 3
inches in parts of Wyoming.
   Snow also fell this morning in parts of Utah. Forecasters said 3
to 6 inches would fall today and be blown by strong northerly winds.
   Northeast winds gusted up to 40 mph this morning at Rock
Springs, Wyo., and Akron, Colo. In California, forecasters posted
wind advisories for parts of Southern California and a gale warning
for the northern coast.
   A heavy snow warning was issued for the eastern foothills of
northern Colorado through tonight. Snow advisories also were posted
in Nebraska's southern panhandle. In addition, forecasters issued
winter storm watches for parts of Wyoming and Kansas.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the
southern Plains across the lower Mississippi Valley, Alabama, the
Tennessee and lower Ohio valleys and the southern Appalachians;
Rain from Oklahoma and eastern Texas into Kentucky and Tennessee;
snow from northern Arizona and the central Rockies into the central
high Plains; windy conditions from Southern California into Western
Texas.
   Highs will be in the 50s or 60s in much of the nation; below
freezing over parts of Colorado and southeast Wyoming; 30s and 40s
from the northern and central Rockies across the northern Plains
into the upper Great Lakes region; 70s and low 80s over California,
the desert Southwest and from southern and eastern Texas to the
southern Atlantic Coast.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 3
degrees at Yellowstone, Wyo., to 75 degrees at Homestead Air Force
Base and Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 42 fair; Buffalo 30 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 55 fair; Cincinnati 45 cloudy; Cleveland 34 partly
cloudy; Detroit 35 fair; Miami 73 partly cloudy; New York 41 fair;
Philadelphia 47 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 39 cloudy; Portland,
Maine, 32 fair; Washington 56 foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck 16 fair; Chicago 34 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
49 drizzle; Denver 27 snow; Des Moines 39 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 43 cloudy; Kansas City 40 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul
36 fair; Nashville 51 rain; New Orleans 67 foggy; St. Louis 45
cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 48 partly cloudy; Anchorage 33 snow; Las
Vegas 50 fair; Los Angeles 58 fair; Phoenix 60 partly cloudy; Salt
Lake City 38 partly cloudy; San Diego 58 fair; San Francisco 62
windy; Seattle 46 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 fair; Toronto 30 fair.
</TEXT>
