<HEAD>Capitol Windows Smashed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADISON, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vandals went on a window-smashing spree at
the Wisconsin Capitol early today, knocking out windows in all four
wings of the building, including the governor's conference room,
security officers said.
   Michael Metcalf, chief of Capitol security, said one man was
apprehended but a second man got away.
   Officer Luke Schneider, who made the arrest, said the man
offered no resistance.
   Metcalf said two men apparently scaled the walls to second-story
balconies and began smashing the windows and high intensity lights
about 1 a.m.
   Thirty-two windows were broken, Metcalf said. It was not known
immediately how many lights were damaged.
   Metcalf estimated it would take between $10,000 aand $20,000 to
repair the damage.
