<HEAD>Cross At Flower Show Rearranged After ACLU Objects</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   City officials rearranged two crosses made from
lillies at Easter flower shows after the American Civil Liberties
Union objected that the displays promoted religion on public
property.
   The two flower crosses had been part of the annual Spring and
Easter Flower Show at the Garfield Park Conservatory and the
Lincoln Park Conservatory, Nancy Kaszak, general attorney for the
Chicago Park District, said Wednesday.
