pillars of flowers climbing almost to the ceiling, she said.
   ``My concern is that the cross put up by a public body on public
property was a violation of the First Amendment,'' said Jane
Whicher, staff counsel for the ACLU in Illinois. ``It shouldn't
have been erected in the first place, but I commend the park
district on removing it so quickly.''
