<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--YouthHanging     03-31 0125</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Youth Hanging,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy Attempts Suicide to Imitate Mass Hangings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old boy was in a coma Thursday
after he tried to hang himself, apparently after he saw a TV news
report of a mass suicide.
   Thaveesak Rojanapitakcheep was sent to Bangkok's Phetchavej
Hospital Tuesday after he was found suspended from a nylon rope,
which was attached to a hook used to hold a punching bag, doctors
said.
   Dr. Suchon Suriyayothin quoted the boy's father, Chaisit
Rojanapitakcheep, as saying that his son often talked about the
highly publicized suicides earlier this month.
   In that incident, six members of a family hanged themselves at
their home in Nonthaburi province near Bangkok in what police
described as a fit of religious fanaticism.
</TEXT>
