<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Zambia-Shooting,0087</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Shot by Police In Food Line Scuffle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman with a baby strapped to her back
was seriously injured when a policeman opened fire on a crowd
fighting for cooking oil and sugar at a state-owned store, police
said Thursday.
   Officer Constantino Nzala said the 24-year-old woman's infant
was unharmed in Wednesday's shooting in the northern town of Ndola.
   Food shortages are common in Zambia, and police are routinely
deployed to keep order when stores receive deliveries.
</TEXT>
