<HEAD>Cher: `Not a Traditional Cookie-Baking Mother'</HEAD>
<NOTE>For release at 6:30 p.m. EST</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cher says she enjoyed making the movie
``Moonstruck'' because it gave her a chance to be part of a big,
traditional family.
   In real life, Cher, 40, lives with a 23-year-old acting student
and copes with the travails of motherhood. Her 11-year-old son,
Elijah Blue, is ``a little superficial,'' and her daughter,
18-year-old Chastity, ``dresses like a bum,'' she complained in an
interview with Film Comment magazine that was reprinted in the
April issue of US.
   ``I'm not a cookie-baking mother,'' said Cher, who is up for the
Academy Award for best actress for her role in ``Moonstruck.''
``Well, that's not true. I am a cookie-baking mother, but I'm not a
traditional cookie-baking mother.''
   Her boyfriend, Robert Camilletti, on the other hand, makes
bagels _ and Cher said it infuriates her when people ``dismiss him
as a bagel maker.''
   ``Do I feel insulted when they dismiss everything about him and
boil it down to that, without a moment's thought to what kind of a
human being he is? Yes. I lived with him when he was a doorman,
when he was a bartender. I don't really care what he is.''
