<HEAD>With PM-World Credit, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is how 112 nations rank for
creditworthiness, according to the latest six-month survey of
bankers by Institutional Investor magazine.
   Approximately 100 banks were asked to rate each country on a
scale of 0 to 100, and the magazine then ranked the nations by
their average rating.
   1. Japan, 94.6
   2. Switzerland, 94.1
