<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
181,925 cars and trucks this week, down from last week's 237,295,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 237,889 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 116,970 cars this
week, compared with 149,951 a week ago and 165,348 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 64,955, compared
with last week's 87,344 and last year's 72,541.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,020 cars this week,
compared with 26,492 last week and 16,670 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 15,319, compared
with 20,266 last week and 17,948 in the same week last year.
